caption: Ordered the PB Piff latte, the Reese’s puffs they put in it were stale, nothing special especially for the price. Burger was cooked well (not temperature wise, just taste wise). Front desk guy wasn’t the nicest.

comfortland never disappoints, ty for existing!

The sandwiches are so delicious, just dont eat them in the car like I did... Bread is so crispy there were crumbs everywhere.
So many funky delicious specials. They currently don’t have outdoor covered seating so don’t go when it’s raining like I did. Or do. It’s honestly so worth it.
Comfortland is amazing, the menu is always changing with new instant favorites. The Donut Diva's creations draw long crowds and happy faces
Insanely delicious and very friendly.
Always a pleasure to order from here.

I have ordered from here 5 times now. All I can say is if you haven’t tried it, you played yourself. The hot chicken sandwich is out of this world. The deserts are creative and incredible. I would travel over 2 hours to eat here if I had to. Do yourself a favor and order the whole menu because there is no wrong choice to be made.

This place has good food. However the service is underwhelming. I'm aware they get super busy on the weekends but that doesn't excuse mistakes. I placed an order for pick up,it was screwed up. Called to have my order fixed, the individual on the other end offered me a refund for the mistake. I called three times over a week for my refund to just be brushed off so here I am letting everyone know to beware of this spot. Don't have high hopes. Comfortland you have lost a customer.

What is there not to love about Comfortland? Best donuts in NYC. Yeah I said it. Fresh ingredients. New and exciting dishes added to their menu on the regular. Crazy sandwiches get thrown in the mix and always slap. My go to spot  now that Queens Comfort caught the R.I.P.s

Nice brunch food and great people around.

Have visited several times trying an array of choices. Have never been dissatisfied. Recently had a piece of a friends stuffed knish, that's right you heard me!. I feel like I’ve seen a lot of hype regarding this place so I had to try it out. Got the Fried chicken sandwich, it was only okay probably a little dry, fries where dry too. Got a Nutella and Oreo milkshake that was really good. Despite being disappointed I’ll likely go back and give it another shot and see, maybe it was an off day.

Let’s just get this out of the way up front- there is not a single place in NYC that makes a better chicken sandwich than Comfortland. And that includes ALL chicken sandwiches. Chicken parm, hot chicken, classic fried chicken- if it is a sandwich that involves chicken, I promise that you will not find it better than how Comfortland prepares it. Scary good. Throw on some stretchy pants and make the trip for it.  If fried chicken isn’t your thing, you’re crazy, but no worries- they have other stuff too. Their burger is good enough to contend with any other, and their cochon po’boy really nails the NOLA flavor profile excellently. Their breakfast sandwiches are so good that my girlfriend once FaceTimed me on a work trip just to talk about one. Yo really can’t miss here.  I can’t say enough good things about Comfortland. My only complaint is that they don’t (regularly) make a mac and cheese- so PLEASE ADD THIS TO YOUR FIRE MENU. That would be next level. Anyway, go here and eat everything because it is all excellent.
Great comfort food, even better people. You have to try their seasonal slushy cocktails.

I’m not proud but I ordered Comfortland two days in a row. The food is amazing. The desserts will blow your mind. I had the Twix donut today and almost cried it was so good. We all need a little comfort these days so thanks to Comfortland for dishing it out so well.

Comfort Land indeed! Biked here form Brooklyn for a Nashville Fried Chicken Sandwich, and couldn't say no to a Slushie Pain Killer. 100% the right choice. This place has far and away the best fried chicken sandwich I've ever had, perfect sauce, pickle, and that brioche bun. It's a hug for your taste-buds.
This place has everything to make you comfortable. Fried chicken, many many sweets, and cute lawn furniture for their outdoor seating. Highly recommend.
Truly the most comfortable place in NYC. Recommend the chicken sandwiches and the luscious deserts. Good times.

Love this place, an amazing bakery to sister restaurant Queens Comfort. Big fan of the vegan Pina colada donut and honestly loved everything I've tried from them. Staff is super nice and helpful making choices to fit your tastes too!

As I have mentioned before in my reviews why the food of any places important the service is key. The service at comfortland is off the charts. The staff is friendly both on the phone to place your order or to call it any questions about your order and upon arrival at said establishment.  The food is also very tasty and delicious.   It is definitely different than anything I've had before here in New York Queens. It is definitely southern food I had the spicy fried chicken sandwich which had pickles and mayonnaise and it was definitely spicy and very tasty.   Their fries are also very unique they have parmesan cheese and oregano and sea salt very tasty..  I would definitely recommend picking up an order of chop cheese empanadas with the spicy ketchup. The meat is seasoned with peppers and they are very delicious.  We had a Nutella shake which is also very good.  I would recommend to try this place out at least once.

I can’t believe I haven’t reviewed COMFORTLAND! This is my favorite spot in the city. Unpretentious and delicious every time. My wife and I come every Saturday we’re in town. Huge shout out to Donut Diva, Donnie, Andy, and KRIS!!

Best donuts and cinnamon rolls omg. The service is awesome and there’s no beating the food. As a *sweets luvr* I am particular about my baked goods and Comfortland knocks it out of the park every time

My home-away-from-home when I'm missing New Orleans. I don't think I've ever had a single bad thing from here. From the sandwiches to breakfast biscuits, to the donuts, coffee, ice cream, and New Orleans style snowballs (they recently got a SnoWizard machine, the gold standard of NOLA snowball making), just pick random stuff off the menu and you're guaranteed something amazing.
Reliable staff for recommendations. The strawberry donut was delish. A bit too much filling for my liking
Awesome food, awesome staff. They are super popular so best to order online for pickup!

I’ve been waiting to come here for many months to try the rainbow crumb cake. It is definitely delicious and doesn’t dishonor the traditional rainbow cookie. It’s very rich so share with a friend! The falafel dog is also very good, all the condiments and toppings make it a tasty vegetarian option. The pulled pork breakfast sandwich is huge, I could only eat half at a time. It was decent and the biscuit exceeded expectations. The almond joy and malted iced coffees are not worth the price. Their normal cold brew is much tastier.
The alcohol slushes are good & so are the  Chopped cheese empanadas and the soft serve ice cream with cotton candy crunches were delicious!

I love a slushy, and this cold brew one may be getting an edge on my memories of Coke slushies. The funfetti scone is really well-balanced - I was expecting a cakier "scone in name only," but it's legitimately a scone and not too sweet.
The chicken sandwich is amazing. My wife is obsessed with the rainbow cake. Even something as "simple" as a bacon egg and cheese is fantastic. Make sure you're hungry when you stop by.

The food here is amazing! Aptly named, the food is the epitome of comfort food. I particularly love their breakfast sandwiches on biscuits - the most moist and delicious biscuits ever! Their donuts are also top-notch. Generous serving sizes, so come/order hungry!
The food the, doughnuts are amazing and soo good and the staff is so friendly! Had a king cake doughnut and it was EVERYTHING!
One of my favorite places in Astoria. Great food, even greater people!
Ordered here for my friends birthday, and it was truly AMAZING. THANK YOU!!!!!
Great desserts which are a little bit pricey, but you get what you pay for which is good quality everything. Get the scone which is the sprinkled object bottom left. Can't go wrong with it.
The most creative food, the most fun atmosphere, the best staff in the whole of the United States. You have to go.
I can't find a better word than wonderful and delicious!  you guys are amazing your food and desserts are unique!  definitely an excellent choice!

*sigh* My first chicken sandwich experience was SOOO good months ago but was so disappointed the second time around. Thin thin slice of chicken in the chicken sandwich. NOTE: Do not go on a Monday! Food shortage and chef seemed like he just gave up from a hard week or something. Donuts still look great and yummy but it is unlikely I will go back to one of my former favorite spots that is in need of revamping and/or re-strategizing of business. I will remember you as you were in the glory days.

One of my favorite spots in Astoria for coffee, dessert, and now lunch too. Their food offerings are always creative and delicious. Items are generally expensive but that doesn't stop me from treating myself or picking something up as a gift. Most recently I tried the donut milk latte (yes, it tastes like a donut!) and the chopped cheese (cooked to perfection). Also appreciate the cool vibe, it's a fun place to hang out.

Incredible food. I’m going to get diabetes from coming here every weekend. So far I've tried 2 of the breakfast sandwiches, one of which even had brisket substituted for pork (because they ran out) and it was still mind-blowing good. They make a lot of donuts and other pastries, and all the ones I've tried so far are fantastic. There's cookies, donuts, mini donuts, Oreo bread pudding, rainbow cake, king cake donuts- you name it. There is a distinct New Orleans theme to the place, and it feels authentically infused with the decor and food. Hot tip: definitely raid the wide and awesome array of hot sauces right next to the kitchen so you can really kick your food up a notch. Without a doubt my favorite place for breakfast and dessert in Queens, if not the universe.
Always amazing food combinations. Great place to come during the day to sip on a coffee, get some work done or even read one of their free comic books they have in location. Bring back FLATTOPPS!!

Great coffee, fresh and creative donuts, tater tots and good breakfast sandwiched --- their definitely worth a 5! The staff is friendly but not intrusive.  We went early on a Sunday (around 830) and had no issues with seating.  We paid cash but it seems as if they are set up for Apple pay.

Comfortland is a relatively new establishment that has a lot of potential. The staff is friendly and their decor is welcoming. Their food is eye-catching, doughnuts are creative, and flavors are on point. Unfortunately, they have a few kinks to work out before really making a push to challenge doughnut plant. I ordered three filled doughnuts, a breakfast sandwich, french toast, tater tots, and coffee. While the doughnuts tasted good, their dough to filling ratio was skewed too heavily in favor of the dough. It seemed like there was only a narrow strip of filling in each doughnut, which was slightly disappointing. The dough seemed a little too dense for my taste as well. Overall, I would call them solid utility doughnuts. The breakfast sandwich was good, though it seems like they run out of biscuits during rushes, leading to an additional 20 minute wait. Something to consider in case one is pressed for time. The interplay between the marinara, egg yolk, and biscuit made for a really enjoyable flavor and textural experience. I would say it was worth the wait.  Unfortunately they mixed up my French toast order and it was another 15 or so minute wait until they made me a new batch. They must have put my order behind other folks because I saw several orders of French toast come out before mine. The music was lovely and made for a relaxing atmosphere. I would prefer it to be a little quieter as the cooks call your name to pick up your sandwiches. In lieu of their yelling over the music or having people crowd around the waiting area (impeding access to the only garbage can and bathrooms) it may be easier to have it be a little quieter so folks can sit at their table and hear their names called. Comortland has a lot of promise and it seems like the staff is really dedicated to making the place successful which is critical for customer satisfaction. While I'm a local, I'll probably continue to head out a little further to doughnut plant if I'm hankering for doughnuts but I hope to come back in a month or two to see their progress.
